.TH "hwicap_get_configuration_register" 9 "hwicap_get_configuration_register" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
hwicap_get_configuration_register \- Query a configuration register.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" hwicap_get_configuration_register
.BI "(struct hwicap_drvdata *drvdata "  ","
.BI "u32 reg "  ","
.BI "u32 *reg_data "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "drvdata" 12
a pointer to the drvdata.
.IP "reg" 12
a constant which represents the configuration
register value to be returned.
.IP "reg_data" 12
returns the value of the register.
.SH "EXAMPLES"
XHI_IDCODE, XHI_FLR.
.SH "RETURN"
'0' on success and failure value on error
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Sends a query packet to the ICAP and then receives the response.
The icap is left in Synched state.
